column5: We are thinking about a trip to Windsor Lake on the Attawapiskat. We usually get our maps from the MNR store (base maps). They don't cover some northern areas including this river. Does anyone have an idea of how to get a decent map? So I can look at it, and dream, through the long winter. thanks
Doesn't give you much detail.. but it would probably help you plan a route. Zoom and zoom and zoom...  http://www.lio.ontario.ca/imf-ows/imf.jsp?site=clupa_en
I'm not sure if this is any more detail then anything you already have or not.http:Windsor Lake
Email me your physical addy and I will send you one compliments of EddieNorth.com
Now there's a guy with a heart. Thank you Eddie!
Nice gesture by Eddie for sure.  Chris for what it's worth I believe you're incorrect in that the 1:50,000 series tops are indeed available and do cover Windsor lake.
